javadoc:
Manages program listing changes and conflicts between the latest versioned program (LATEST) and the modified program (MY) being checked into version control.
Listing changes include:
  • bytes
  • code units [instructions and data]
  • equates
  • functions
  • symbols
  • references [memory, stack, and external]
  • comments [plate, pre, end-of-line, repeatable, and post]/li>
  • properties
  • bookmarks

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment:
Manages listing changes and conflicts between the latest versioned
 program and the modified program being checked into version control.

params.name: mergeManager
params.comment: the top level merge manager for merging a program version.

params.name: resultPgm
params.comment:
the program to be updated with the result of the merge.
 This is the program that will actually get checked in.

params.name: originalPgm
params.comment: the program that was checked out.

params.name: latestPgm
params.comment: the latest checked-in version of the program.

params.name: myPgm
params.comment: the program requesting to be checked in.

params.name: latestChanges
params.comment: the address set of changes between original and latest versioned program.

params.name: myChanges
params.comment: the address set of changes between original and my modified program.

Sets up the change address sets, Diffs between the various program versions,

methods.name: initMergeInfo
methods.comment:
Sets up the change address sets, Diffs between the various program versions,

methods.javadoc:
Creates all of the individual mergers that are used by the ListingMergeManager.
 Each of these listing mergers will autoMerge() non-conflicting changes and will
 determine conflicts. The conflicts are handled later by calling manualMerge().
methods.name: initializeMergers
methods.comment:
Creates all of the individual mergers that are used by the ListingMergeManager.
 Each of these listing mergers will autoMerge() non-conflicting changes and will
 determine conflicts. The conflicts are handled later by calling manualMerge().

methods.name: autoMerge
methods.comment:
Performs an automatic merge of My changes that are not conflicts for all the mergers
 specified. Each of the merger's autoMerge is performed in the order they
 are found in the array. Each autoMerge will cause that merger to determine conflicts.
 Note: This method should be called a single time for any set of listing mergers
 and then be followed by the mergeConflicts() call to resolve conflicts.

params.name: mergers
params.comment: the listing mergers to be auto-merged.

params.name: monitor
params.comment: indicates progress to user and allows cancel.

throws.comment: if programs can't be compared using Diff.
if bytes can't be merged.
if the user cancels the merge.

methods.javadoc:
For JUnit testing only, set the option for resolving a conflict.
@param decision CANCELED, ASK_USER, PICK_LATEST, PICK_MY, PICK_ORIGINAL
methods.name: setConflictDecision
methods.comment: For JUnit testing only, set the option for resolving a conflict.

params.name: decision
params.comment: CANCELED, ASK_USER, PICK_LATEST, PICK_MY, PICK_ORIGINAL

methods.name: mergeConflicts
methods.comment:
Performs a manual merge of the Listing conflicts for all the mergers
 specified. The addresses with conflicts will be resolved in order
 from minimum address to maximum address.
 At each address all conflicts are resolved before moving to the next address.
 Note: Call the autoMerge() method before this method in order to
 determine the conflicts.

params.name: mergers
params.comment: the listing mergers whose conflicts are to be merged.

params.name: monitor
params.comment: indicates progress to user and allows cancel.

throws.comment: if bytes can't be merged.
if the user cancels the merge.

methods.name: getTotalNumConflicts
methods.comment: Gets the number of Listing conflicts to resolve at the indicated address.

params.name: mergers
params.comment: the mergers whose address based conflicts are of interest.

params.name: addr
params.comment: the address

return.comment: the number of Listing conflicts at the address

methods.name: getListingConflicts
methods.comment:
Gets the set of addresses where conflicts need to be resolved in the listing
 by each of the merger's specified.

params.name: mergers
params.comment: the mergers whose address based conflicts are of interest.

return.comment: the set of addresses with conflicts.

methods.javadoc:
Returns the listing merge panel.
 This panel displays all four programs for a versioned merge.
 Above the listings in conflict information.
 Below the listings is a conflict panel for the user to resolve conflicts.
@return the listing merge conflict panel
methods.name: getListingMergePanel
methods.comment:
Returns the listing merge panel.
 This panel displays all four programs for a versioned merge.
 Above the listings in conflict information.
 Below the listings is a conflict panel for the user to resolve conflicts.

methods.javadoc:
Returns the conflict information panel. This panel appears above
 the listings on a listing merge conflict dialog. It indicates the type
 of conflict, address (if applicable), how many conflicts, etc.
@return the conflict information panel.
methods.name: getConflictInfoPanel
methods.comment:
Returns the conflict information panel. This panel appears above
 the listings on a listing merge conflict dialog. It indicates the type
 of conflict, address (if applicable), how many conflicts, etc.

methods.name: resolveNamespace
methods.comment:
This method allows other listing merge managers to resolve a namespace
 via the symbol merge manager. This is because the symbol merge manager
 actually merges namespaces and best knows how to resolve them.
 It also keeps track of how they have been resolved.

params.name: srcProgram
params.comment: the program version that the namespace to be resolved is coming from.

params.name: srcNamespace
params.comment: the namespace to be resolved

throws.comment:
if the name space can't be resolved due
 to a name conflict that can't be dealt with.

if the name space is not validly named
 for the result program.

return.comment: the namespace from the result program version

fields.javadoc:
The four programs used in a versioned program merge.
RESULT: the program to be updated with the result of the merge. This is the program that will actually get checked in.
ORIGINAL: the program that was checked out.
LATEST: the latest checked-in version of the program.
MY: the program requesting to be checked in.
fields.name: programs
fields.comment:
The four programs used in a versioned program merge.
 RESULT: the program to be updated with the result of the merge.
 This is the program that will actually get checked in.
 ORIGINAL: the program that was checked out.
 LATEST: the latest checked-in version of the program.
 MY: the program requesting to be checked in.
